<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Demo OAuth2 Client</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/oauth2-client.css">

    <!-- jQuery (necessary for Bootstrap's JavaScript plugins) -->
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.1.1.min.js"></script>
    <!-- material design lite -->
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/materialize/0.98.1/css/materialize.min.css">
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/materialize/0.98.1/js/materialize.min.js"></script>

</head>
<!--<body style="background-color:#eee;">-->
<body>

<nav class="blue-grey" role="navigation">
    <div class="nav-wrapper container">
        <a id="logo-container" href="#" class="brand-logo">OAuth 2 Client</a>

        <ul id="nav-mobile" class="right hide-on-med-and-down">
        </ul>
    </div>
</nav>

<div class="container">

    <!-- Page Content goes here -->

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
                <h2 class="center orange-text"><i class="material-icons">flash_on</i></h2>
                <h5 class="center">Resource Owner Password Flow</h5>

                <p class="light">Resource Owner Password flow allows a login by transmitting
                    username and password from the page - typically by using a
                    script. Thus it can integrate very well into an existing design.
                    The access token will not be directly visible to the client
                    server.</p>
                <div class="center">
                    <a href="/auth_code" class="waves-effect waves-light btn blue-grey">Try now</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
                <h2 class="center orange-text"><i class="material-icons">group</i></h2>
                <h5 class="center">Authorization Code Flow</h5>

                <p class="light">Authorization Code provides a safe way to communicate between
                    the authorization server and the client server. The access
                    token will only be revealed to the client server.</p>
                <div class="center">
                    <a href="/auth_code" class="waves-effect waves-light btn blue-grey">Try now</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
                <h2 class="center orange-text"><i class="material-icons">settings</i></h2>
                <h5 class="center">Implicit Grant Flow</h5>

                <p class="light">Implicit client flow puts the access token directly in the
                    url of callback redirect. The access token can be read by javascript
                    on the page.</p>
                <div class="center">
                    <a href="/implicit" class="waves-effect waves-light btn blue-grey">
                        Try now
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

</body>
</html>